    • Method Detail

      • mutate

        java.lang.Object mutate(java.lang.reflect.Type type,
                        java.lang.Object currentValue,
                        java.lang.Object parent,
                        PopulatorContext config)
        Called to mutate the instance passed in currentValue, or create a new instance if the current value is null.
        Parameters:
        type - the type of current value
        currentValue - the current value. Implementations are free to mutate this instance and return it, as opposed to creating a new instance, if the type is mutable.
        parent - the parent object to current value. This can be of use when working with inner classes.
        config - the populator config
        Returns:
        the mutated version of currentValue. This can be the same instance as currentValue or a new instance.
